# Audit fix (loop iter 45, 2026-05-25): without this file, `pnpm format:check`
# checked 67 vendored Arc sample files + lockfiles + build outputs, exited
# non-zero, and would have blocked any CI gate that ran prettier.

# Vendored sample repos (Arc/Circle reference implementations) — owned upstream
resources/repos/**

# Build + cache outputs
**/.next/**
**/.next-*/**
**/dist/**
**/.turbo/**
**/coverage/**
**/out/**

# Lockfiles
**/pnpm-lock.yaml
**/package-lock.json
**/yarn.lock
**/foundry.lock

# Dependencies
**/node_modules/**

# Generated / external assets
**/*.min.js
**/*.min.css
designer/**/index.html

# Foundry artifacts
packages/contracts/cache/**
packages/contracts/out/**
packages/contracts/lib/**
packages/contracts/broadcast/**

# Iter 48: Solidity formatting is owned by `forge fmt` (Foundry standard),
# not prettier-plugin-solidity. The two disagree (303 file diffs) and
# fighting them creates infinite churn. Exclude *.sol so each formatter
# owns its language.
**/*.sol

